# Text Style for Generated Content

When writing user-facing text (copy, descriptions, UI strings, documentation):

**Never use:**
- **Em dashes (—)** — Use a comma, period, or rephrase instead.
- **Hyphenated compounds** like "hands-on", "real-time" — Use separate words ("hands on", "real time") or rephrase.

**Examples:**
- ❌ "add to—but no one can erase" → ✅ "add to, but no one can erase"
- ❌ "hands-on demos" → ✅ "hands on demos" or "interactive demos"
- ❌ "real-time updates" → ✅ "real time updates" or "live updates"
